and other top officials.

11:00.326 --> 11:05.665 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
It alleges that Russia used
covert operations
to steal material from the
Democratic Party

11:05.698 --> 11:11.004 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
and others, and disseminated it
through media
organizations that it controls
and through

11:11.037 --> 11:12.872 align:left position:12.5%,start line:93.33% size:87.5%
third-party groups.

11:12.906 --> 11:18.311 align:left position:12.5%,start line:73.33% size:87.5%
It called the campaign a
significant escalation
of Russian efforts to -- quote
-- "undermine

11:18.344 --> 11:21.648 align:left position:0%,start line:86.67% size:100%
the U.S.-led liberal democratic
order."

11:21.681 --> 11:26.452 align:left position:12.5%,start line:73.33% size:87.5%
For more on the report's
findings and its
effects, I'm joined from Capitol
Hill by California

11:26.486 --> 11:28.221 align:left position:0%,start line:93.33% size:100%
Representative Adam Schiff.

11:28.254 --> 11:31.524 align:left position:0%,start line:80% size:100%
He is the top Democrat on the
House Intelligence
Committee.

11:31.558 --> 11:36.396 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
And, for the record, we called
every current
Republican member serving on the
Senate and

11:36.429 --> 11:38.298 align:left position:0%,start line:93.33% size:100%
House Intelligence Committees.

11:38.331 --> 11:39.732 align:left position:12.5%,start line:93.33% size:87.5%
None was available.

11:39.766 --> 11:43.670 align:left position:0%,start line:80% size:100%
Adam Schiff, Congressman Schiff,
thank you
very much for joining us.

11:43.703 --> 11:50.376 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
Now, this report says it has
high confidence
that President Vladimir Putin
personally ordered

11:50.410 --> 11:53.713 align:left position:0%,start line:86.67% size:100%
this campaign to interfere with
the U.S. election.

11:53.746 --> 12:00.053 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
It doesn't say how it knows
that, but after
you were briefed and have read
the classified

12:00.086 --> 12:02.088 align:left position:0%,start line:80% size:100%
report, are you confident that
that's what
happened?

12:02.121 --> 12:03.356 align:left position:37.5%,start line:93.33% size:62.5%
REP.

12:03.389 --> 12:05.091 align:left position:0%,start line:80% size:100%
ADAM SCHIFF (D), California:
Well, I am very
confident in it.

12:05.124 --> 12:08.561 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
And I think all the members of
the Intelligence
Committee, Democrats and
Republicans, are

12:08.595 --> 12:12.131 align:left position:0%,start line:80% size:100%
confident in the conclusions
about the Russian
involvement.

12:12.165 --> 12:16.703 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
I have been on the committee now
for almost
10 years, and this is among the
best documented,

12:16.736 --> 12:22.108 align:left position:12.5%,start line:73.33% size:87.5%
most ironclad, I think,
intelligence reports
that I have seen on any major
issue.

12:22.141 --> 12:26.713 align:left position:0%,start line:80% size:100%
If this doesn't persuade Donald
Trump about
the facts, nothing will.

12:26.746 --> 12:31.517 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
JUDY WOODRUFF: The report, also,
Congressman
Schiff, says the Russians
developed what they

12:31.551 --> 12:35.388 align:left position:0%,start line:86.67% size:100%
call a clear preference for
Donald Trump.

12:35.421 --> 12:36.389 align:left position:37.5%,start line:93.33% size:62.5%
How so?

12:36.422 --> 12:38.057 align:left position:37.5%,start line:93.33% size:62.5%
REP.

12:38.091 --> 12:40.259 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
ADAM SCHIFF: Well, there are
many reasons
why the Russians prefer Donald
Trump.

12:40.293 --> 12:43.997 align:left position:0%,start line:80% size:100%
I think, in the first instance,
they wanted
to tear down Secretary Clinton.

12:44.030 --> 12:49.802 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
They, I think, despised her
remarks about
the flawed 2011 elections in
Russia.

12:49.836 --> 12:53.673 align:left position:0%,start line:80% size:100%
They feared that she would be
very tough on
Russia in terms of sanctions.

12:53.706 --> 12:57.043 align:left position:0%,start line:80% size:100%
Donald Trump, on the other hand,
they had
every reason to want.

12:57.076 --> 13:02.281 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
It was somebody who belittled
NATO, who praised
Putin, who I think would be much
more amenable

13:02.315 --> 13:05.451 align:left position:0%,start line:80% size:100%
to their policy in Syria, where
they bomb
civilians.

13:05.485 --> 13:09.055 align:left position:0%,start line:80% size:100%
So there were a lot of reasons
for them to
prefer Donald Trump.

13:09.088 --> 13:14.227 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
It was their aspiration, as the
report makes
clear, to help him and to hurt
her.

13:14.260 --> 13:19.065 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
JUDY WOODRUFF: The report also
points out
that the Russian -- how the
Russian military

13:19.098 --> 13:26.439 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
intelligence passed along this
information
to WikiLeaks, the so-called
transparency organization.

13:26.472 --> 13:31.277 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
We know Julian Assange, the
founder of WikiLeaks,
say they didn't get it from the
Russians.

13:31.310 --> 13:37.617 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
What evidence is there in the
report that
there was collaboration between
the Russians

13:37.650 --> 13:38.618 align:left position:25%,start line:93.33% size:75%
and WikiLeaks?

13:38.651 --> 13:40.386 align:left position:37.5%,start line:93.33% size:62.5%
REP.

13:40.420 --> 13:42.155 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
ADAM SCHIFF: You know, I can't
go into that
evidence, because that's really
the heart

13:42.188 --> 13:44.590 align:left position:0%,start line:86.67% size:100%
and soul of the classified
report.

13:44.624 --> 13:47.660 align:left position:0%,start line:86.67% size:100%
But I can say I think the case
is very powerful.

13:47.694 --> 13:51.397 align:left position:0%,start line:86.67% size:100%
WikiLeaks was a useful medium
for the Russians.

13:51.431 --> 13:56.335 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
They had a little more distance
or deniability
with WikiLeaks than they did
with their other

13:56.369 --> 13:58.471 align:left position:0%,start line:86.67% size:100%
cutouts, so they made ample use
of it.

13:58.504 --> 14:04.310 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
I think Julian Assange knows
this, or he is
affirmatively trying to stick
his head in

14:04.343 --> 14:05.678 align:left position:25%,start line:93.33% size:75%
the sand.

14:05.712 --> 14:07.547 align:left position:0%,start line:80% size:100%
But, nonetheless, it was a very
useful platform
for the Russians.

14:07.580 --> 14:12.852 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
JUDY WOODRUFF: Before this
report became public
and, in fact, before
president-elect Trump

14:12.885 --> 14:21.127 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
was briefed, he said that this
whole thing
is a political witch-hunt, the
findings by

14:21.160 --> 14:23.563 align:left position:0%,start line:93.33% size:100%
the U.S. intelligence community.

14:23.596 --> 14:24.764 align:left position:0%,start line:93.33% size:100%
What's your reaction to that?

14:24.797 --> 14:25.765 align:left position:37.5%,start line:93.33% size:62.5%
REP.

14:25.798 --> 14:27.700 align:left position:0%,start line:86.67% size:100%
ADAM SCHIFF: My reaction is
this.

14:27.734 --> 14:32.572 align:left position:12.5%,start line:73.33% size:87.5%
We need Democrats and
Republicans in Congress
to work together to fashion a
very comprehensive

14:32.605 --> 14:37.710 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
pushback to Russia, not just the
cyber-hacking,
but their bribery of officials
in Europe,

14:37.744 --> 14:42.281 align:left position:0%,start line:80% size:100%
their social media campaign,
their overt media
campaign.

14:42.315 --> 14:48.087 align:left position:12.5%,start line:73.33% size:87.5%
All of the dirty tricks,
basically, the Russians
employ to tear down liberal
democracy, we

14:48.121 --> 14:52.592 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
need to work together on a
bipartisan basis,
and we need the new president's
help.

14:52.625 --> 14:54.627 align:left position:12.5%,start line:93.33% size:87.5%
We can't do it alone.

14:54.660 --> 14:57.930 align:left position:0%,start line:80% size:100%
And that has to begin by his
acknowledgment
of the facts.

14:57.964 --> 15:02.468 align:left position:0%,start line:80% size:100%
We need him to lead the liberal
democratic
order around the world.

15:02.502 --> 15:06.906 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
No other nation can do that the
way we can,
and it's going to be very hard
for Congress

15:06.939 --> 15:08.708 align:left position:0%,start line:93.33% size:100%
to do it over his opposition.

15:08.741 --> 15:13.246 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
JUDY WOODRUFF: Well, one of the
other -- one
of the comments he made after
the briefing

15:13.279 --> 15:19.986 align:left position:12.5%,start line:73.33% size:87.5%
was he pointed out and
emphasized, he said
he appreciated the briefing, but
he emphasized

15:20.019 --> 15:25.992 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
that the alleged Russian action
had, in his
words, absolutely no effect on
the outcome

15:26.025 --> 15:27.827 align:left position:25%,start line:93.33% size:75%
of the election.

15:27.860 --> 15:33.266 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
Now, my reading of what was made
public from
this report is that they didn't
examine whether

15:33.299 --> 15:36.602 align:left position:0%,start line:86.67% size:100%
the hacking affected the outcome
of the election.

15:36.636 --> 15:37.603 align:left position:37.5%,start line:93.33% size:62.5%
REP.

15:37.637 --> 15:39.438 align:left position:0%,start line:86.67% size:100%
ADAM SCHIFF: That's exactly
right.

15:39.472 --> 15:41.641 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
And I think that was very
misleading of the
president-elect to suggest that
this report

15:41.674 --> 15:46.179 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
or the presentation said there
was no outcome
effect, no effect on the
election itself.

15:46.212 --> 15:53.152 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
It is true there is no evidence
that the tampering
with voter machines or tampering
with voter

15:53.186 --> 15:56.556 align:left position:0%,start line:80% size:100%
registrations or any of like
that affected
the counting of the votes.

15:56.589 --> 15:58.057 align:left position:25%,start line:93.33% size:75%
That's true.

15:58.090 --> 16:00.526 align:left position:0%,start line:80% size:100%
That's not the same thing as
saying there
was no impact on the outcome.

16:00.560 --> 16:05.698 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
Clearly, the daily dumping of
information
that was damaging to Secretary
Clinton and

16:05.731 --> 16:09.001 align:left position:0%,start line:86.67% size:100%
helpful to Donald Trump was
hugely consequential.

16:09.035 --> 16:13.039 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
And it's not the intelligence
community's
place to say whether this was
determinative

16:13.072 --> 16:14.040 align:left position:37.5%,start line:93.33% size:62.5%
or not.

16:14.073 --> 16:15.908 align:left position:0%,start line:93.33% size:100%
And, indeed, that's unknowable.

16:15.942 --> 16:20.179 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
But that claim was completely
unsupported
by the report or the briefing he
got today.

16:20.213 --> 16:24.650 align:left position:12.5%,start line:73.33% size:87.5%
JUDY WOODRUFF: We know,
Congressman Schiff,
that President Obama did take
some moves,

16:24.684 --> 16:32.258 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
took measures against the
Russian intelligence
community just in the last few
days.

16:32.291 --> 16:35.228 align:left position:0%,start line:86.67% size:100%
Yesterday, I interviewed Vice
President Biden.

16:35.261 --> 16:38.998 align:left position:0%,start line:80% size:100%
He said other steps have been
taken that are
not publicly known.

16:39.031 --> 16:43.236 align:left position:0%,start line:80% size:100%
Is it your sense that the U.S.
is responding
appropriately?

16:43.269 --> 16:45.137 align:left position:12.5%,start line:93.33% size:87.5%
Should more be done?

16:45.171 --> 16:49.876 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
What should Americans -- what
should America
-- what should the United States
be prepared

16:49.909 --> 16:51.477 align:left position:0%,start line:93.33% size:100%
to do as a result of this?

16:51.510 --> 16:53.312 align:left position:37.5%,start line:93.33% size:62.5%
REP.

16:53.346 --> 16:56.349 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
ADAM SCHIFF: I think what has
been done so
far by the current
administration is a first

16:56.382 --> 16:57.350 align:left position:37.5%,start line:93.33% size:62.5%
step.

16:57.383 --> 16:59.585 align:left position:0%,start line:86.67% size:100%
It is by no means, I think,
sufficient.

16:59.619 --> 17:01.988 align:left position:0%,start line:80% size:100%
We need to work in Congress on a
bipartisan
basis.

17:02.021 --> 17:07.593 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
We have reached out on the
Democratic side
to Senator McCain and Graham on
a package

17:07.627 --> 17:11.864 align:left position:0%,start line:80% size:100%
of sanctions, broader sanctions,
to make the
Russians pay a price.

17:11.898 --> 17:19.605 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
But even beyond that, we need a
comprehensive
approach to what is a very
successful, well-funded

17:19.639 --> 17:25.645 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
Russian effort, through a
variety of vectors,
through, as I mentioned, bribery
of people,

17:25.678 --> 17:30.850 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
and their media platforms, their
hacking,
the publishing of fake news, the
publishing

17:30.883 --> 17:35.821 align:left position:0%,start line:80% size:100%
of bogus documents, we need to
push back against
all of that.

17:35.855 --> 17:37.924 align:left position:0%,start line:80% size:100%
It's a threat to the German
elections coming
up.

17:37.957 --> 17:41.727 align:left position:0%,start line:80% size:100%
It's a threat to our French
allies, our NATO
allies.

17:41.761 --> 17:44.997 align:left position:0%,start line:86.67% size:100%
And we need a comprehensive and
hard pushback.

17:45.031 --> 17:47.333 align:left position:0%,start line:86.67% size:100%
It's the only thing the Russians
understand.

17:47.366 --> 17:49.502 align:left position:0%,start line:86.67% size:100%
It's the only thing that will
deter them.

17:49.535 --> 17:53.572 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
JUDY WOODRUFF: Congressman Adam
Schiff, the
ranking Democrat on the House
Intelligence

17:53.606 --> 17:55.408 align:left position:0%,start line:80% size:100%
Committee, we thank you very
much for talking
with us.

17:55.441 --> 17:56.409 align:left position:37.5%,start line:93.33% size:62.5%
REP.

17:56.442 --> 17:58.277 align:left position:12.5%,start line:93.33% size:87.5%
ADAM SCHIFF: Thank you.

17:58.311 --> 18:04.417 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
JUDY WOODRUFF: And you can read
the full declassified
intelligence report on our Web
site.

18:04.450 --> 18:15.594 align:left position:0%,start line:93.33% size:100%
That's at PBS.org/NewsHour.

18:15.628 --> 18:18.698 align:left position:0%,start line:80% size:100%
And now to my interview with
Secretary of
State John Kerry.

18:18.731 --> 18:23.469 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
I sat down with him earlier
today at the State
Department, before the public
release of that

18:23.502 --> 18:25.404 align:left position:0%,start line:93.33% size:100%
intelligence report on Russia.

18:25.438 --> 18:30.810 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
But I began by asking, now that
we have confirmation
Russia interfered in the
election, does that

18:30.843 --> 18:36.415 align:left position:12.5%,start line:80% size:87.5%
fundamentally change
Washington's relationship
with Moscow?

18:36.449 --> 18:38.584 align:left position:0%,start line:80% size:100%
Secretary of State John Kerry,
thank you very
much for talking with us.

18:38.617 --> 18:39.585 align:left position:0%,start line:86.67% size:100%
JOHN KERRY, U.S. Secretary of
State: My pleasure.

18:39.618 --> 18:41.454 align:left position:25%,start line:93.33% size:75%
Thank you.

18:41.487 --> 18:45.324 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
JUDY WOODRUFF: So, now that it
has been confirmed
that the Russians interfered
aggressively

18:45.358 --> 18:50.563 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
in the U.S. election, does this
represent
a fundamental change in the
United States'

18:50.596 --> 18:51.831 align:left position:0%,start line:93.33% size:100%
relationship with Russia?

18:51.864 --> 18:54.367 align:left position:0%,start line:86.67% size:100%
JOHN KERRY: Well, that remains
to be determined.

18:54.400 --> 18:58.137 align:left position:0%,start line:80% size:100%
It certainly represents a major
challenge
in that relationship.

18:58.170 --> 18:59.672 align:left position:12.5%,start line:93.33% size:87.5%
It's a hostile act.

18:59.705 --> 19:03.943 align:left position:0%,start line:80% size:100%
It has serious consequences, and
we're going
to have to work that through.

19:03.976 --> 19:05.978 align:left position:25%,start line:93.33% size:75%
And I say we.

19:06.012 --> 19:09.982 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
I mean the United States, the
next administration
is going to have to approach
Russia very clearly

19:10.016 --> 19:11.417 align:left position:0%,start line:93.33% size:100%
understanding what has happened.

19:11.450 --> 19:15.855 align:left position:0%,start line:80% size:100%
JUDY WOODRUFF: Do you think more
needs to
be done to retaliate as of now?

19:15.888 --> 19:22.161 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
JOHN KERRY: Well, I think that
President Obama
made it clear that we would
retaliate at a

19:22.194 --> 19:25.464 align:left position:0%,start line:86.67% size:100%
time of our choosing and ways of
our choosing.

19:25.498 --> 19:28.934 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
And that means some of them, the
public will
know about, some of them, they
will not know

19:28.968 --> 19:30.770 align:left position:37.5%,start line:93.33% size:62.5%
about.

19:30.803 --> 19:35.474 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
Obviously, with two weeks left,
I think that
the administration coming in is
going to have

19:35.508 --> 19:38.711 align:left position:0%,start line:80% size:100%
to make some judgments of its
own about what
the next steps will be.

19:38.744 --> 19:43.516 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
JUDY WOODRUFF: So, it's reported
the Russians
were celebrating the election of
Donald Trump.

19:43.549 --> 19:44.984 align:left position:0%,start line:93.33% size:100%
Why would they be celebrating?

19:45.017 --> 19:46.052 align:left position:12.5%,start line:93.33% size:87.5%
What do you think?

19:46.085 --> 19:47.887 align:left position:0%,start line:86.67% size:100%
JOHN KERRY: I'm not going to
speculate.

19:47.920 --> 19:50.356 align:left position:12.5%,start line:86.67% size:87.5%
I really think it's too
important.

19:50.389 --> 19:52.391 align:left position:0%,start line:86.67% size:100%
And I just am not going to
speculate.

19:52.425 --> 19:55.194 align:left position:0%,start line:86.67% size:100%
I think there has been a lot of
news articles.

19:55.227 --> 19:58.664 align:left position:0%,start line:80% size:100%
You all have been covering this
for some period
of time.

19:58.697 --> 20:03.169 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
People are going to draw their
own judgments,
but I'm not going to add to that
speculation.

20:03.202 --> 20:05.271 align:left position:0%,start line:80% size:100%
JUDY WOODRUFF: What do you think
Vladimir
Putin wants?

20:05.304 --> 20:08.808 align:left position:0%,start line:80% size:100%
You have been dealing with him
for a long
time.

20:08.841 --> 20:10.042 align:left position:0%,start line:93.33% size:100%
What do you think he's after?

20:10.076 --> 20:12.511 align:left position:0%,start line:86.67% size:100%
JOHN KERRY: Well, he's after a
lot of things.

20:12.545 --> 20:14.080 align:left position:0%,start line:93.33% size:100%
There are a lot of motivations.

20:14.113 --> 20:19.985 align:left position:0%,start line:80% size:100%
He obviously has agreed with us
on some things
and disagreed with us on others.

20:20.019 --> 20:26.725 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
And we managed to find common
ground and work
together effectively on the Iran
nuclear agreement,

20:26.759 --> 20:31.831 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
where Russia assumed major
responsibilities
to try to get the agreement done
and to make

20:31.864 --> 20:33.632 align:left position:37.5%,start line:93.33% size:62.5%
it work.

20:33.666 --> 20:38.737 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
So I can give you a long list of
things where
Russia and President Putin have
found common

20:38.771 --> 20:40.706 align:left position:0%,start line:86.67% size:100%
ground and worked with the
United States.

20:40.739 --> 20:47.913 align:left position:12.5%,start line:73.33% size:87.5%
But, on Ukraine, on the
implementation of
the Minsk agreement, on Syria,
we have obviously

20:47.947 --> 20:52.184 align:left position:0%,start line:80% size:100%
not been able to find the same
kind of common
ground, despite good efforts.

20:52.218 --> 20:56.956 align:left position:0%,start line:80% size:100%
And those are problems that are
going to continue
into the next administration.

20:56.989 --> 21:05.030 align:left position:12.5%,start line:73.33% size:87.5%
My hope is the next
administration will approach
Russia strategically, with a
clear purpose

21:05.064 --> 21:11.036 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
of trying to find more common
ground, but
without giving up on fundamental
values and

21:11.070 --> 21:14.773 align:left position:0%,start line:80% size:100%
principles that are at the core
of the United
States' foreign policy.

21:14.807 --> 21:17.276 align:left position:0%,start line:80% size:100%
JUDY WOODRUFF: Well, are you
concerned that
that could happen?

21:17.309 --> 21:22.414 align:left position:0%,start line:80% size:100%
