successor, the designate,
Rex Tillerson.

21:22.448 --> 21:28.654 align:left position:0%,start line:80% size:100%
Does he have the same view of
Russian intentions
that you do?

21:28.687 --> 21:33.225 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
JOHN KERRY: Well, he and I are
going to sit
down, actually, I think next
week, and have

21:33.259 --> 21:37.163 align:left position:0%,start line:80% size:100%
an opportunity to really debrief
and to go
into these subjects.

21:37.196 --> 21:44.103 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
So, I can't comment on what his
approach is
going to be or what he's
thinking at this

21:44.136 --> 21:46.005 align:left position:12.5%,start line:93.33% size:87.5%
moment about that.

21:46.038 --> 21:54.947 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
I can tell you that I think
there is an opportunity
here, still, for president-elect
Trump and

21:54.980 --> 22:00.152 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
then President Trump to try to
reach out to
Russia and see whether or not
they can put

22:00.186 --> 22:06.492 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
to test the proposition that we
could find
things in which we can agree and
perhaps on

22:06.525 --> 22:10.596 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
some things on which we're going
to agree
to disagree, but, nevertheless,
put the world

22:10.629 --> 22:12.431 align:left position:12.5%,start line:93.33% size:87.5%
in a better place.

22:12.464 --> 22:14.934 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
JUDY WOODRUFF: But, at this
moment, you're
not worried that the incoming
administration

22:14.967 --> 22:16.402 align:left position:25%,start line:93.33% size:75%
could be naive?

22:16.435 --> 22:20.172 align:left position:12.5%,start line:80% size:87.5%
JOHN KERRY: Well, I have
questions, like everybody
has questions, Judy.

22:20.206 --> 22:26.745 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
But I'm not -- as secretary of
state, it's
inappropriate for me to start
speculating

22:26.779 --> 22:29.615 align:left position:0%,start line:80% size:100%
publicly or get caught up in the
day-to-day
back-and-forth.

22:29.648 --> 22:31.116 align:left position:12.5%,start line:93.33% size:87.5%
I don't want to do that.

22:31.150 --> 22:33.619 align:left position:0%,start line:93.33% size:100%
I think it's inappropriate.

22:33.652 --> 22:41.827 align:left position:12.5%,start line:73.33% size:87.5%
I think there are clear
strategic possibilities
that, if the new administration
pursues correctly,

22:41.860 --> 22:50.302 align:left position:12.5%,start line:73.33% size:87.5%
could open up avenues of
cooperation and reduce
tensions and perhaps put to test
whether or

22:50.336 --> 22:56.942 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
not there could be, you know, a
more improved
day-to-day relationship between
us.

22:56.976 --> 22:58.377 align:left position:12.5%,start line:93.33% size:87.5%
JUDY WOODRUFF: Syria.

22:58.410 --> 23:01.080 align:left position:0%,start line:80% size:100%
I happened to sit down yesterday
with Vice
President Biden.

23:01.113 --> 23:05.017 align:left position:12.5%,start line:80% size:87.5%
I asked him whether that
represented a failure
for the United States.

23:05.050 --> 23:06.952 align:left position:25%,start line:93.33% size:75%
He said no.

23:06.986 --> 23:12.258 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
My question to you is, if it's
not a failure,
doesn't it at least, beyond
being a humanitarian

23:12.291 --> 23:18.697 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
disaster, represent an enormous
missed opportunity
for the United States to shape
events in that

23:18.731 --> 23:19.965 align:left position:12.5%,start line:93.33% size:87.5%
part of the world?

23:19.999 --> 23:23.702 align:left position:0%,start line:80% size:100%
JOHN KERRY: Well, we did shape
events to a
certain degree.

23:23.736 --> 23:29.475 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
It is certainly going to be
debated whether
or not they were shaped enough
or whether

23:29.508 --> 23:34.346 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
certain options that might have
shaped them
differently were taken or not
taken.

23:34.380 --> 23:39.785 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
But I agree with the vice
president that the
fact that we were not able,
which is a disappointment,

23:39.818 --> 23:46.825 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
clearly, to push the parties
into a place
where they made a different set
of choices,

23:46.859 --> 23:48.460 align:left position:12.5%,start line:93.33% size:87.5%
that's disappointing.

23:48.494 --> 23:52.798 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
But I don't think it represents,
you know,
some sort of failure on our
part.

23:52.831 --> 23:55.200 align:left position:0%,start line:86.67% size:100%
You can try and try and push
people.

23:55.234 --> 24:00.439 align:left position:0%,start line:80% size:100%
The old saying, you can lead a
horse to water,
but you can't make it drink.

24:00.472 --> 24:06.345 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
And here, we led people to
water, the water
of peace proposition, the water
of Geneva

24:06.378 --> 24:07.846 align:left position:25%,start line:93.33% size:75%
of a process.

24:07.880 --> 24:11.817 align:left position:12.5%,start line:80% size:87.5%
We laid out through our
leadership the International
Syria Support Group.

24:11.850 --> 24:13.786 align:left position:0%,start line:93.33% size:100%
We brought Iran to the table.

24:13.819 --> 24:15.654 align:left position:0%,start line:93.33% size:100%
We brought Russia to the table.

24:15.688 --> 24:24.063 align:left position:0%,start line:80% size:100%
We had assurances that Assad
would do certain
things.

24:24.096 --> 24:25.097 align:left position:25%,start line:93.33% size:75%
He didn't.

24:25.130 --> 24:26.799 align:left position:25%,start line:93.33% size:75%
He chose not to.

24:26.832 --> 24:31.537 align:left position:12.5%,start line:73.33% size:87.5%
So, the Russians failed,
actually, to deliver
Assad in a way that they said he
would.

24:31.570 --> 24:37.476 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
The Iranians failed to deliver
the process
that they said they would,
because they continued

24:37.509 --> 24:43.582 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
to prop him up in ways that went
way beyond
the agreement that had been
reached in the

24:43.615 --> 24:48.120 align:left position:0%,start line:80% size:100%
Geneva agreement to try to come
to a political
resolution.

24:48.153 --> 24:51.023 align:left position:0%,start line:86.67% size:100%
So, look, did the whole process
fail?

24:51.056 --> 24:54.193 align:left position:0%,start line:80% size:100%
Did the international community
fail to solve
it?

24:54.226 --> 24:55.894 align:left position:25%,start line:93.33% size:75%
Yes, profoundly.

24:55.928 --> 25:00.265 align:left position:0%,start line:80% size:100%
But was that a specific failure
of the United
States?

25:00.299 --> 25:03.836 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
History will debate whether some
choices might
have been made or not made that
might have

25:03.869 --> 25:10.142 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
altered that, but I don't think
it falls exclusively
on us that this problem hasn't
been solved.

25:10.175 --> 25:15.848 align:left position:12.5%,start line:73.33% size:87.5%
JUDY WOODRUFF: Are U.S.
interests advanced
with the way things stand today
in Syria?

25:15.881 --> 25:18.951 align:left position:0%,start line:86.67% size:100%
JOHN KERRY: With the way they
stand today?

25:18.984 --> 25:24.690 align:left position:0%,start line:80% size:100%
No, nobody's interests are
served by what's
happening in Syria today.

25:24.723 --> 25:25.891 align:left position:12.5%,start line:93.33% size:87.5%
It's a catastrophe.

25:25.924 --> 25:29.495 align:left position:0%,start line:80% size:100%
It's the worst human catastrophe
since World
War II.

25:29.528 --> 25:36.168 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
And, as I said just now, it
represents a failure
of the entire international
community to come

25:36.201 --> 25:38.036 align:left position:0%,start line:93.33% size:100%
to grips with solving it.

25:38.070 --> 25:41.306 align:left position:0%,start line:80% size:100%
And it's a tragedy for the
people who have
been caught in the middle.

25:41.340 --> 25:47.413 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
But I am proud of what our
administration
has done, of what we did day to
day to try

25:47.446 --> 25:49.381 align:left position:0%,start line:93.33% size:100%
to get a cease-fire in place.

25:49.415 --> 25:54.586 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
I am proud that we are the
largest donor of
humanitarian assistance for
refugees.

25:54.620 --> 25:57.523 align:left position:0%,start line:86.67% size:100%
I am proud of what we did with
the ISSG.

25:57.556 --> 26:03.195 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
And I regret that we were not
able to be successful
in getting the parties to
Geneva.

26:03.228 --> 26:08.801 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
But I deeply believe that we are
on the cusp
of seeing that happen over the
course of the

26:08.834 --> 26:15.474 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
next months, and that it will be
the framework
that we put in place that is
ultimately going

26:15.507 --> 26:20.646 align:left position:0%,start line:80% size:100%
to be the structure around which
peace in
Syria is built.

26:20.679 --> 26:23.415 align:left position:0%,start line:80% size:100%
JUDY WOODRUFF: Several other
countries I want
to mention very quickly.

26:23.449 --> 26:25.217 align:left position:37.5%,start line:93.33% size:62.5%
Israel.

26:25.250 --> 26:29.021 align:left position:12.5%,start line:73.33% size:87.5%
