29:52.991 --> 29:54.126 align:left position:0%,start line:93.33% size:100%
What are we to make of this?

29:54.159 --> 29:56.328 align:left position:0%,start line:86.67% size:100%
Does it change the way we look
at this election?

29:56.361 --> 29:59.464 align:left position:0%,start line:80% size:100%
MARK SHIELDS: I don't know if it
changes the
way we look at it, Judy.

29:59.498 --> 30:04.569 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
It certainly changes the way we
look at the
United States' relationship with
Russia, I

30:04.603 --> 30:12.244 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
think, and in this sense, that
the intelligence
community said it made these
findings with

30:12.277 --> 30:14.012 align:left position:25%,start line:93.33% size:75%
high confidence.

30:14.046 --> 30:22.421 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
Ever since the weapons of mass
destruction
era and the decision on invading
Iraq, the

30:22.454 --> 30:26.024 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
intelligence community has been
very, very
careful to avoid high
confidence.

30:26.058 --> 30:29.227 align:left position:0%,start line:80% size:100%
That's saying, we really believe
this to be
true.

30:29.261 --> 30:31.797 align:left position:0%,start line:93.33% size:100%
They have been more tentative.

30:31.830 --> 30:32.798 align:left position:12.5%,start line:93.33% size:87.5%
There was no question.

30:32.831 --> 30:34.533 align:left position:0%,start line:86.67% size:100%
They were unequivocal and
emphatic.

30:34.566 --> 30:39.604 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
Every American ought to be
angry, ought to
be concerned that an unfriendly
nation, a

30:39.638 --> 30:47.879 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
nation that has cooperated with
us certain
places, but doesn't wish us
well, sought to

30:47.913 --> 30:53.552 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
sabotage American democracy,
American confidence
in our own democratic
institutions, and to

30:53.585 --> 30:56.455 align:left position:0%,start line:86.67% size:100%
influence the outcome of the
election.

30:56.488 --> 31:00.025 align:left position:0%,start line:86.67% size:100%
That's a cause of concern and
worry and anger.

31:00.058 --> 31:04.563 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
And I would hope that we would
respond, not
as Democrats or Republicans, but
as Americans,

31:04.596 --> 31:05.864 align:left position:0%,start line:86.67% size:100%
to make sure it never happens
again.

31:05.897 --> 31:07.966 align:left position:0%,start line:80% size:100%
JUDY WOODRUFF: David, how should
Americans
look at this?

31:07.999 --> 31:10.035 align:left position:0%,start line:80% size:100%
DAVID BROOKS: I agree with that,
with anger,
with shock.

31:10.068 --> 31:14.206 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
We have sort of gotten used to
the idea, because
of the news leaks before this
report.

31:14.239 --> 31:18.477 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
But the idea that Russia felt
emboldened and
apparently fearless to go into
our election

31:18.510 --> 31:23.482 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
and manipulate our own election
process, whether
successfully or not, is a sign
that they are

31:23.515 --> 31:25.016 align:left position:0%,start line:86.67% size:100%
outside the norms of normal
society.

31:25.050 --> 31:26.017 align:left position:0%,start line:93.33% size:100%
There's always statecraft.

31:26.051 --> 31:27.819 align:left position:0%,start line:93.33% size:100%
There's always disinformation.

31:27.853 --> 31:31.857 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
But this is a step up, a Russia
that feels
completely free to do this, a
Putin who feels

31:31.890 --> 31:36.194 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
completely free to do this,
without fear of
penalty, and so far paying
little penalty.

31:36.228 --> 31:40.699 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
Partly, it's motivated, I think,
by animus
